Aegis Holds Talks With Ipsos on Synovate Sale, Telegraph Says

-- B y   E m m a   C h a r l t o n
-- 
2011-06-05T11:55:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-05/ipsos-may-buy-aegis-s-821-million-synovate-research-unit-telegraph-says.html
Aegis Group Plc (AGS)  held talks with
polling company  Ipsos (IPS)  SA about selling its 500 million-pound
($821 million) market research unit, Synovate, the Sunday
Telegraph  reported , without saying where it got the information.  The two companies met last week to discuss the sale, the
newspaper reported. Market research firm  GfK SE (GFK) ,  Publicis Groupe
SA (PUB)  and WPP Plc will probably also be interested in Synovate, the
Sunday Telegraph said.  UBS AG (UBSN)  is advising Ipsos, while Greenhill
& Co. is advising Aegis, the newspaper said.  Susanna Voyle, a spokeswoman for Aegis Group, declined to
comment. Catherine Roussies, a spokeswoman for Ipsos, didnâ€™t
immediately return calls and an e-mail seeking comment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
